## What is loxilb

loxilb is a cloud-native networking/security stack built from grounds up using eBPF at its core. loxilb aims to provide the following :

-  Service type external load-balancer for kubernetes (hence gets the name loxilb)
-  Optimized SRv6 implementation in eBPF 
-  Make GTP tunnels first class citizens of the Linux world 
-  Data-path based on eBPF/XDP (GPL licensed)
-  Control-plane is based on go-language (Apache licensed)
-  Seamlessly integrated with goBGP based routing stack

## How to build/run

Step1 - Install package dependencies 

# sudo apt install clang llvm libelf-dev gcc-multilib libpcap-dev
# sudo apt install linux-tools-$(uname -r)
# sudo apt install elfutils dwarves

Step2 - Make 

# make

Step3 - Run 

# sudo go run .

or 

# sudo ./loxilb 
